Propensity score estimation- logistic regression, random Forest, CART

1. Logistic Regression

1-a. LR-ps estimation

df_lo=df

log_reg_ps=glm(treat~ .-outcome, family = "binomial", data=df)
df_lo$ps=log_reg_ps$fitted.values

df_lo %>% head()
##   age sex treat subseq outcome blood_diff        ps
## 1  31   0     1    140       0         14 0.8519067
## 2  35   1     1    124       1          9 0.8295720
## 3  27   1     0    101       0          9 0.4788117
## 4  66   0     0    112       1         -6 0.8274391
## 5  54   1     1     90       0          1 0.8711348
## 6  35   1     1    104       0         11 0.8536802

1-b. LR-weighting

zi=df_lo$treat
yi=df_lo$outcome
e=df_lo$ps

df_lo$w<-ifelse(df_lo$treat==1,1/df_lo$ps,1/(1-df_lo$ps))
df_lo %>% head()
##   age sex treat subseq outcome blood_diff        ps        w
## 1  31   0     1    140       0         14 0.8519067 1.173838
## 2  35   1     1    124       1          9 0.8295720 1.205441
## 3  27   1     0    101       0          9 0.4788117 1.918692
## 4  66   0     0    112       1         -6 0.8274391 5.795055
## 5  54   1     1     90       0          1 0.8711348 1.147928
## 6  35   1     1    104       0         11 0.8536802 1.171399
ATE_ipw_log=mean(zi*yi/e)-mean((1-zi)*yi/(1-e))
ATE_ipw_log
## [1] -0.1232716
ATE_sipw_log=sum(zi*yi/e)/sum(zi/e)-sum((1-zi)*yi/(1-e))/sum((1-zi)/(1-e))
ATE_sipw_log
## [1] -0.008681161

1-c.LR-Evaluate

propensity score .

par(mfcol=c(1,2))
ggplot(data=df_lo, aes(x=ps))+geom_density(aes(fill=factor(treat)),alpha=0.3)

ggplot(data=df_lo, aes(x=ps, weight=w))+geom_density(aes(fill=factor(treat)),alpha=0.3) 

cov_balance_lo=data.frame(rep(0),row.names = "Logistic Regression")

for(i in colnames(df)){
  if(i!="treat" & i!="outcome"){
#    print(df1[i])
    t_weighted_mean=mean((df[i]*df_lo$w)[df$treat==1,])
    c_weighted_mean=mean((df[i]*df_lo$w)[df$treat==0,])
    weighted_mean_diff=abs(t_weighted_mean-c_weighted_mean)
    asam=weighted_mean_diff/sd((df[i]*df_lo$w)[df$treat==1,])
    cov_balance_lo[i]=asam
  }
}
cov_balance_lo=cov_balance_lo[,-1]
cov_balance_lo
##                          age      sex   subseq blood_diff
## Logistic Regression 7.568573 2.395685 9.923526  0.5602369
cov_balance_lo$ASAM=apply(cov_balance_lo,1,mean)
cov_balance_lo["ASAM"]
##                         ASAM
## Logistic Regression 5.112005

#install.packages("randomForest")

library(randomForest)
## randomForest 4.7-1.1
## Type rfNews() to see new features/changes/bug fixes.

df_rf=df
rf=randomForest(treat~ .-treat-outcome, data=df_rf,ntree=100, type= "regression")
## Warning in randomForest.default(m, y, ...): The response has five or fewer
## unique values. Are you sure you want to do regression?
df_rf$ps=predict(rf)

3. CART

3-a. CART-ps estimation

library(rpart)

#control = rpart.control(minbucket = 2)
df_c<-df

cart=rpart(treat~ .-outcome, 
           data=df_c ,
           method='poisson',
           control = rpart.control(minsplit = 30))
#summary(cart2)
cart$cptable
##           CP nsplit  rel error    xerror       xstd
